SIMPLE: manakin
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manakin
<hw>Man"a*kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. & G.
<ets>manakin</ets>; prob. the native name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous small birds belonging to <gen>Pipra</gen>,
<gen>Manacus</gen>, and other genera of the family <fam>Pipridae</fam>.
They are mostly natives of Central and South America. Some are
bright-colored, and others have the wings and tail curiously ornamented.
The name is sometimes applied to related birds of other
families.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manakin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Manakin
<hw>Man"a*kin</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dwarf. See
<er>Manikin</er>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manannan</ent>⟦br⟧
